Many counties anticipate increased energy demand from the planned data centers than the current/ existing demand.

The data is highly skewed to the left, let's do a log graph

```{r}
ggplot(data = county_totals |>
         filter(current_mw > 0, planned_mw >0),
       aes( x = current_mw,
            y = planned_mw,
            ))+
  geom_point(color = "steelblue", alpha = 0.6)+
  geom_abline(slope = 1, intercept = 0, linetype = "dashed")+ # reference line - Counties above the line have more planned than current energy demand
  scale_x_log10()+
  scale_y_log10()+
  labs( title = "Current vs Planned Data Center Energy Demand Capacity (log - log scale)",
        x = "Current energy demand (mw)",
        y = "Planned energy demand (mw)",
        caption = "Source: National Laboratory of the Rockies Accelerating Speed to Power Data viewer")+
  theme_light()

```

The planned energy demand for data centers exceeds the current energy demand.

